There is one local doctor whose surgery is in Hawkshead village, 9 - 9.30 a.m. and 5 - 6 p.m. most days. Prescriptions are dispensed at the chemist's shop, also in Hawkshead. There is one resident district nurse. A child welfare clinic is held monthly in a mobile caravan, and health visitors will visit homes when necessary. The Wednesday club for the elderly meets each week in the old school, and a chiropodist visits the club each month.
Housebound patients may receive visits from the doctor, a dentist, an optician, an occupational therapist and a speech therapist.
The area is served by the{South {Cumbria District Health Authority. }
